Ad Text:
A rare and exciting opportunity has become available for a full-time Data Quality Engineer to join our Technology team in either of the below 3 offices in Australia with the opportunity to work from home.

Melbourne
Sydney
Brisbane

Who We Are – Viridian Financial Group

Viridian Financial Group was established in 2015 by a team who understood the life changing power of financial advice. Viridian now has over 450 professionals empowering clients and advice firms across Australia through Financial Advice, Lending, Investments and Digital Solutions.

We are united in purpose, and our strength lies in working together to deliver expert guidance tailored to meet the ever-changing needs of our clients’ and the advice industry.

About the Role

While the Data Quality Engineer is a part of the Technology team, you will work closely with the Portfolio Management team to identify and resolve inconsistencies and refine data validation processes. You’ll also collaborate to automate anomaly detection, address data issues, and ensure compliance with data governance standards.

Key Responsibilities

You will be working closely with developers, product managers, and business stakeholders, as you:

Monitor, analyse, and validate large datasets to identify inconsistencies, anomalies, and errors.
Investigate root causes of data discrepancies and implement corrective actions.
Develop and refine data validation processes to enhance data quality.
Collaborate with teams to resolve data integrity issues.
Support the automation of anomaly detection and error correction processes.
Ensure compliance with data governance standards and best practices.

Working at Viridian

In 2022, the firm achieved B Corp status with a B Impact score of 99.4 and in 2025 was recertified, increasing that score to 151. Viridian has been recognised as one “Best for the World” in the Workers Impact category, placing Viridian in the top 5% score by putting in place exemplary employee-friendly practices, such as ownership opportunities, job flexibility, and fair-chance hiring policies.

You will have access to a range of benefits centered around community and inclusivity:

Unique and generous leave benefits, such as Birthday Leave, Wellness Day, 13-week’s Primary Careers Leave and the ability to purchase additional Annual Leave.
Flexible work options with the ability to work from home.
Participation in our Viridian Team Community Program.
Discounted Medibank Corporate Health Cover.
Employee Assistance providing free and confidential counselling services to all employees and their families.

Knowledge, Skills & Experience

Bachelor’s degree in Data Science, Statistics, Computer Science, Finance, Economics, or a related field.
Industry experience in finance, desirable but not mandatory.
Experience with programming languages such as Python
Excellent problem-solving skills and attention to detail.
High level of proficiency in Microsoft Excel.
Strong knowledge of SQL and experience with relational databases.

To Apply

We warmly welcome candidates who meet the above points under “knowledge, skills & experience” to apply.

Please note, this position will require a Police Check. Applicants must be legally entitled to work in Australia. This advert will close Wednesday 11th March 2026, 9.00pm however shortlisting will commence immediately.

At Viridian, we believe in the strength of diversity and the power of inclusion. We celebrate the unique contributions of every individual, regardless of their background, culture, nationality, or ability. We cultivate an environment where everyone feels valued, respected, and empowered to thrive. We especially encourage Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander people, along with individuals from all cultural backgrounds and those with disabilities, to apply and join our team in contributing to our shared success.

Job Title: Software Engineer Manager (MERN stack, AWS DevOps)
Ad Text:
The Role

As Software Development Manager, you will provide technical leadership, delivery ownership, and people leadership for our development teams. You will ensure we deliver high-quality, scalable SaaS solutions predictably, while continuously improving our Agile maturity and engineering practices.

You’ll work closely with Product and senior stakeholders to align technical decisions with commercial outcomes, while fostering a culture of wellbeing, growth, and accountability.




What You'll Be Doing

Lead and mentor software engineers, providing hands-on technical guidance and coaching

Own Agile delivery: sprint planning, execution, retrospectives, and continuous improvement

Ensure delivery of secure, scalable SaaS solutions aligned to customer and business needs

Review designs and solutions to maintain high standards of quality, security, performance, and resilience

Identify risks, bottlenecks, and technical debt early and act decisively

Drive improvements in engineering practices, tooling, and delivery cadence

Partner with Product and stakeholders to translate strategy into executable delivery

Support career development, performance growth, and succession planning within the team

Foster a high-performance culture grounded in trust, wellbeing, and accountability




What We Are Looking For (Must-Have)

Proven experience leading teams in a Commercial SaaS environment (this is essential)

Strong background as a software engineer who has progressed into leadership

Hands-on experience with Agile development (Scrum/Kanban) and sprint-based delivery

Demonstrated success delivering commercial, customer-facing software products

Deep technical credibility, able to challenge designs, guide architecture, and assess trade-offs

Experience coaching engineers across varying levels of seniority

Strong communication skills, able to align technical teams with business priorities

Strong AWS experience with a clear focus on cost-conscious engineering and cloud cost optimisation and modern DevOps practices




Nice to Have

Experience in FinTech, RegTech, or other regulated environments

Interest in emerging technologies such as AI/LLMs in SaaS products

Experience applying SRE principles to improve reliability, availability, incident response, and production stability in SaaS systems




What Success Looks Like

Predictable, high-quality delivery with fewer late-stage surprises

Engaged engineers who feel supported, challenged, and clear on their growth paths

Continuous improvement in Agile maturity and engineering practices

Early identification and resolution of technical and delivery risks




Welcome to MVSI!

We are a dynamic team of 70+ professionals, spread across the Globe with offices in Australia, EMEA, the US and the Philippines. Our innovative SaaS product is trusted by banks, Fintech’s, and crypto services worldwide to manage their AML/KYC Compliance requirements. We have always harnessed the power of cutting-edge technology and are expanding the exciting realm of LLM (think ChatGPT) to further elevate our offerings. Our company culture is built on a foundation of support and commitment to career development.

We truly value our people and invite you to join us to experience all that we have to offer!

This role is ideal for a hands-on technical leader who has grown from software engineering into people leadership and thrives in modern SaaS, Agile environments.




Why Join MVSI?

Get an awesome career! Ours is a specialised industry, and experience is in short supply.

Global impact – Your work directly supports financial crime prevention worldwide

True SaaS scale – Build and evolve a commercial, multi-partner platform

Modern engineering culture – Agile, continuous improvement, pragmatic delivery

Career growth – A company that actively invests in leadership and capability development

Supportive environment – High standards without burnout; people genuinely matter here

Who are we? 

We are the leading online platform for comparing and buying business insurance. 

Not to toot our own horn, but we’re shaking things up in the SME business insurance market! We’re all about making it easy and efficient for small businesses to get the perfect coverage they need to stay protected. Say goodbye to headaches and hello to hassle-free insurance!

Role Purpose?

The purpose of this role is to contribute to changing how BizCover operates using data to drive decisions and exceed our strategic growth objectives.

Responsibilities:

Own end-to-end delivery of data pipelines, models, and tests 
Implement reusable patterns and model structures in MSSQL, dbt Cloud, and Snowflake 
Monitor data quality, lineage, and job health 
Collaborate cross-functionally to define scalable data solutions 


Requirements


Ideally would have 4-6 years of experience.
Technical experience with Snowflake, Fivetran, dbt Cloud, MSSQL 
Ability to model data using best practices 
Proficiency in writing tests, implementing observability, and improving reliability 
Strong documentation and technical communication skills
Hands-on experience using AI-assisted development tools (e.g., SQL/dbt copilots, LLMs for documentation, testing, or refactoring) to improve productivity and code quality. 
Interest in learning and adopting emerging AI capabilities within the modern data stack. 


Benefits


Hybrid working model with flexibility to work from home and the office (if not based in Sydney, the role will be fully remote)
Exciting and rewarding team culture
Quarterly recognition awards
Business Casual dress code
Rewarding Employee Incentive Program
Employee benefits package
Growing company with progression opportunities

We are an equal opportunity employer and we do not discriminate on the basis of race, color, religion, sex, sexual orientation, gender identity, national origin, age, disability, or any other protected status. We encourage applications from people of all backgrounds, identities, and perspectives. We are committed to creating a diverse and inclusive workplace where everyone can thrive and grow.

The Company:

A household Australian name has an immediate opportunity for an Azure Data Engineer to work on a variety of data initiatives within a small team. You will be Sydney based and be able to work in the office up to 4 days per week.


The Role:

Work closely with the data architect, key business stakeholders and the wider data & technology team to design, develop & enhance critical business applications.
Be involved in data architecture and data infrastructure decisions.
Design & implement data models and support the BI team for reporting & analytic solutions. 
Develop & support ETL for large data-sets.
Design and develop scalable data pipelines, ensuring seamless data flow and optimisation.
Mentoring of more junior colleagues.
Your Skillset:

Proven hands-on experience in developing data solutions in Snowflake and other cloud-based data platforms
Azure environment, particularly ADF for ETL & Fabric.
SQL, Python
Strong knowledge of data warehousing & Data modelling
Experience in data migration & integration & optimisation
Enjoys working within a collaborative team and able to build good relationships with business and technical stakeholders. 
You must have full working rights within Australia and be Sydney based to be considered for this opportunity.

About Us

Crossmuller Systems Integration is a multi-disciplined engineering leader specialising in the design, build, and integration of advanced industrial systems across various customers and industries. Our project-based work spans diverse sectors including Food and Beverage, Data Centres, Manufacturing, Recycling, and Warehouse Automation.

The Role

We are seeking an experienced and motivated Systems Engineer to play a key role in the delivery of our projects. You will be responsible for the technical design, implementation, and commissioning of complex integration solutions. Your ability to understand the big picture while managing the technical details will be key to successfully interfacing with both our internal teams and our clients.

This role is ideal for a competent technical professional who excels in a project environment and is looking to grow their career, with a clear path towards technical leadership and mentorship opportunities.


Key Responsibilities:

Design, develop, and deploy integrated control systems, including PLC, SCADA, HMI, and industrial networking.

Architect and implement system solutions that meet client requirements, often involving integration with existing MES, ERP, and database applications.

Manage the technical aspects of projects, including system architecture design, specification writing, and code development.

Participation in commissioning activities, system troubleshooting, and providing client training.

Act as a technical point of contact for clients and collaborate effectively with other engineering departments to ensure seamless project execution.

Provide guidance and share knowledge with graduate engineers, contributing to the team's collective expertise.

 

About You

You are an experienced engineer with a proven track record in systems integration within industrial environments.

You thrive in a project-based role where no two days are the same, and you enjoy the challenge of adapting to different technical requirements and scopes.

You are a confident problem-solver who can work autonomously to lead commissioning activities and interact directly with clients.

You have a strong understanding of how different systems (electrical, mechanical, IT) interact and are skilled at making them work together.

You possess strong communication and collaboration skills, and the ability to guide others is looked upon favourably as a key to future growth within our team.

 

Career Growth

At Crossmuller, we are committed to the professional development of our staff. For the right candidate, this role offers a clear pathway for advancement. We value and will support your growth into technical leadership and mentorship positions, where you can take on greater responsibility for project deliverables and guide the next generation of engineers.

 

Essential Skills and Experience:

3+ years of experience in a similar systems integration, automation, or controls role.

Proven proficiency with industrial control platforms (e.g., Siemens TIA Portal, Rockwell Studio 5000/ControlLogix, Schneider EcoStruxure).

Strong experience with SCADA/HMI systems (e.g., Inductive Automation Ignition, Aveva System Platform, Aveva Citect/Plant SCADA, Siemens WinCC, Rockwell FactoryTalk View).

Solid understanding of industrial networking (switches, routers, VLANs, firewall configurations) and communication protocols (Modbus. BACnet, OPC UA, MQTT).

Experience in database integration (SQL) and higher-level programming languages (e.g., C#, Python) is highly regarded.

Excellent verbal and written communication skills, with the ability to produce clear technical documentation.

Eligibility Requirements:

A degree in Software, Mechatronic, Electrical, or a related engineering field.

Available to work full-time and willing to travel to client sites for commissioning as required.

Possess a valid driver's licence.

Australian Citizenship or Permanent Residency.

About the Role:
Join a dynamic team delivering enterprise AI and cloud transformation with Databricks as a strategic focus. You will play a key role in shaping innovative data engineering solutions, working closely with clients to remove technical blockers and accelerate adoption of best practices across big data platforms.

The organisation is growing fast, in a scale-up phase with significant opportunities for growth and significant exposure to the Databricks team. If Databricks is a passion for you, this is an organisation that will have you working alongside some of the most experienced and strongest technical professionals in the space.

Why This Role is Unique:
● Senior-level role, working with enterprise level customers on large scale projects.
● Be part of a hands-on, deeply technical team recognized for transformative impact on clients data architecture and AI transformation journeys.
● Engage with rapidly evolving GenAI technologies, modern data practices, and cloud-native architectures that push the boundaries of what’s possible.
● Supported by transparent leadership and a culture focused on mentorship, continuous learning, and technical excellence.
● Enjoy work-life balance through flexible arrangements while contributing to projects delivering real business outcomes globally.

Your Impact and Responsibilities:
● Lead and contribute hands-on to projects using Databricks, Apache Spark, and related big data tools to build scalable, high-performing pipelines and platforms.
● Collaborate with diverse teams to design and implement data architectures that simplify complex business problems.
● Drive adoption of modern CI/CD, MLOps, and DevOps pipelines, ensuring automation and quality at scale.
● Advise customers on strategic technical decisions, challenge assumptions, and guide teams in overcoming roadblocks.
● Mentor peers and foster a culture of knowledge sharing to maintain a reputation for technical excellence.
● Work across cloud platforms integrating Databricks with Hadoop, Flink, Presto, Redshift, and others.

Required Experience & Qualifications:
● 5+ years of experience in consulting.
● Completed Data Engineering Professional certification.
● Minimum 6-8+ projects delivered with hands-on experience in development on databricks.
● Current knowledge across the breadth of Databricks product and platform.
● Expertise with cloud data architectures.

Preferred Skills:
● Experience with BigQuery, Synapse, Redshift, Hadoop, Flink, Presto.
● Knowledge of modern CI/CD, automation, MLOps, and DevOps best practices.
● Strong interpersonal skills with an ability to challenge and lead technical strategy.
● Passion for educating others and evangelizing technical best practices.

What You’ll Gain:
● First class exposure to the Databricks team.
● Work across genuine enterprise level projects.
● Exposure to some of the most advanced AI and data engineering projects shaping enterprise capabilities.
● A collaborative, mentor-rich environment focused on professional growth and transparent leadership.
● Flexible working options, competitive remuneration, and a culture that values technical contribution and innovation.

As a trusted recruitment partner to government and industry, we pride ourselves on connecting exceptional people with roles where they can truly make an impact.

Success

Machine Learning Engineer

Permanent, Full-time | Hybrid
Sydney / Melbourne

The Role

We're looking for a Machine Learning Engineer (Junior to Mid-Level) to join our Analytics team. You'll design, develop and operate machine learning solutions that support real clinical and operational cases across I-MED.

Working alongside Senior ML Engineers, Data Scientists and Clinical stakeholders, you'll contribute across the full ML lifecycle, from model development through to production deployment in a highly regulated healthcare environment.

What You'll Be Doing


Develop, train and evaluate machine learning models
Deploy models into scalable, production-grade services
Contribute to batch and/or streaming ML systems
Integrate ML services with enterprise and clinical platforms via APIs
Implement monitoring, logging, testing and alerting
Support model lifecycle activities including versioning and retraining
Collaborate in Agile teams with Data, Engineering, Product and Clinical partners

What We're Looking For


2-3+ years' experience in software engineering with applied machine learning
Strong understanding of ML fundamentals, feature engineering and evaluation
Hands-on experience deploying and operating ML models in production
Proficiency in Python, SQL and Linux
Experience with batch or streaming ML systems
Familiarity with CI/CD pipelines

Highly desirable:


ML Ops or ML engineering practices
Docker and containerised workloads
Cloud ML platforms (AWS, GCP or Azure)
Streaming or near real-time data pipelines
Experience in regulated environments (healthcare, finance)
Exposure to Generative AI (LLMs, RAG, agent workflows)
REST/gRPC services or Kubernetes experience

About I-MED

I-MED Radiology Network is Australia and New Zealand's largest diagnostic imaging network, offering medical imaging and radiology services including x-ray, PET, CT, MRI, Nuclear Medicine, Ultrasound, Mammography and interventional procedures.

At I-MED Radiology Network there is a strong belief that we can be the most respected and trusted medical imaging specialists in the world. That's our vision, underpinned by our purpose - to help save lives and reduce uncertainty. We strive to be the provider of choice, providing answers to health questions and delivering high quality care and service to our patients and referrers, every time.

Why I-MED?


Work on AI that directly supports patient care
Hybrid working and flexible locations
Strong technical mentorship and career growth
Purpose-driven, collaborative culture

This is a great opportunity to grow your ML engineering career while delivering AI solutions that make a meaningful difference in healthcare.
